To this end, the WPCA offices and Newlands Cricket Ground, is under lockdown until further notice. CAPE TOWN - The Western Province Cricket Association (WPCA) has heeded the call by President Cyril Ramaphosa to take swift, purposeful and collective action immediately relating to the coronavirus. To this end, the WPCA offices and Newlands Cricket Ground, is under lockdown until further notice. This means that the majority of its staff will work remotely, all club, youth and any other form of cricket (CPL, etc.) is cancelled and all board and subcommittee meetings are cancelled. The public is kindly requested not to visit Newlands Cricket Ground during this time to exercise social distancing and prevent the spread of the virus. An assessment will be made every week to consider the ongoing need to remain under lockdown.